Looking for a tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Spicy Prawn Pasta with Courgettes in just 20 minutes for a balanced and tasty meal.

== Preparation ==

Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @courgette{1} then slice into rounds about 1cm thick.

Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @red chilli{1} lengthways, deseed then slice thinly.

== Chargrilled Courgettes ==

Heat a large #frying pan{} on a high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the courgette and cook on each side until starting to char, ~{2-3%mins} per side.

Remove from the pan to a #chopping board{} and allow to cool.

== Pasta ==

Once the water for the pasta is boiling.

Add the @linguine{200%g} and simmer until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with @vegetable oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Sauce ==

Meanwhile return the frying pan to medium high heat with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{drizzle}.

When hot, add the garlic and half of the chilli and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @tomato passata{1} and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @water{50%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1}.

Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%mins}.

== Prawns and Assembly ==

Add the @king prawns{150%g} to the tomato sauce, stir together and simmer until cooked, ~{4-5%mins}.

IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly chop up the courgette and add to a #small bowl{} with the spring onion and remaining chilli.

Add the drained pasta to the pan of tomato sauce.

Mix well to combined, then season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the charred courgette. Enjoy!